## Code quality (single owner for `src/**/*.ts`)

When you add or modify code under `src/`:

1. **Fix issues in files you touched** — resolve Biome errors and any new warnings inline (see `agent-os/skills/code-smells-and-best-practices/SKILL.md`; warning details in `agent-os/skills/lint-warnings-handler/SKILL.md`).
2. **Do not re-run full-repo checks by default** — Husky pre-commit (`lint-staged`, `typecheck`, `validate:domain`) and CI (`pnpm validate`) already enforce lint, format, and types. Run `pnpm lint` / `pnpm typecheck` only when the hook or CI failed, or before a large PR-sized change.
3. **Do not ask the user** how to fix warnings — apply the skills and move on.
